$ chexa8_axial_force.bdf
$ Single CHEXA8 unit cube — axial extension in z
$
$ Geometry: 1 m × 1 m × 1 m cube
$ Material: E = 1e6 Pa, nu = 0.3
$ Load:     1000 N total in +z, split evenly over 4 top-face corner nodes
$ BCs:      minimal — fix T3 of all bottom-face nodes (z=0),
$           fix T1+T2 of node 1, fix T2 of node 2
$
$ Hand calculation (trilinear element is exact for linear fields):
$   A = 1 m², L = 1 m
$   δ = F*L / (E*A) = 1000*1 / (1e6*1) = 1e-3 m
$   σ_z = F / A = 1000 Pa
$   Poisson: ε_x = ε_y = -nu * δ/L = -3e-4
$            u at (1,0,1) = -nu * (F/EA) * x = -3e-4 m
$
SOL 101
CEND
SUBCASE 1
  LABEL = CHEXA8 AXIAL FORCE
  LOAD = 1
  SPC = 1
  DISPLACEMENT = ALL
  STRESS = ALL
BEGIN BULK
PARAM,CSVOUT,YES
$ Nodes: unit cube
$ Bottom face (z=0): nodes 1-4
GRID,1,,0.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,2,,1.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,3,,1.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,4,,0.0,1.0,0.0
$ Top face (z=1): nodes 5-8
GRID,5,,0.0,0.0,1.0
GRID,6,,1.0,0.0,1.0
GRID,7,,1.0,1.0,1.0
GRID,8,,0.0,1.0,1.0
$ Material
MAT1,1,1.0E6,,0.3
$ Solid property (SRI formulation)
PSOLID,1,1
$ Single CHEXA8 element
CHEXA,1,1,1,2,3,4,5,6,+
+,7,8
$ BCs: fix T3 of all bottom-face nodes (prevents z translation and tilt)
$      fix T1+T2 of node 1 (prevents lateral RBM)
$      fix T2 of node 2 (prevents rotation about z)
SPC1,1,3,1
SPC1,1,3,2
SPC1,1,3,3
SPC1,1,3,4
SPC1,1,12,1
SPC1,1,2,2
$ Load: 250 N in +z at each top-face node = 1000 N total
FORCE,1,5,0,250.0,0.0,0.0,1.0
FORCE,1,6,0,250.0,0.0,0.0,1.0
FORCE,1,7,0,250.0,0.0,0.0,1.0
FORCE,1,8,0,250.0,0.0,0.0,1.0
ENDDATA
